<div id="explanation" class="container">
  <div class="panel panel-default" style="background-color:#ABC9ED">
    <div class="panel-body">
      <h2>The game</h2>
      <p>
        A game has three roles: guesser, reader and judge. Every game contains a story of some kind,
        which is available to the reader and the judge. During each round, the reader or the guesser
        gets to ask a question about the document. Both the reader and guesser must answer that question.
        After they both have answered, they can see each other's answers. The judge will receive both answers
        anonymously, and needs to select which answer he/she thinks originated from the reader. The 3 players
        are not allowed to communicate outside of the game app.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        <h2>Game score</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Judge and reader gain 1 point whenever the judge successfully identifies
            an answer given by the guesser. </li>
          <li>The reader gains 1 point whenever the judge fails to correctly identify
            the guesser's answer.</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<p>
  <center>
    <button id="queue_button" type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#queue_modal">Queue for a game</button>
    <button id="central_dequeue" type="button" class="btn btn-warning btn-lg"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-fire" style="color:blue"></span> Dequeue <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-fire" style="color:blue"></button>
  </center>
</p>

